From 862ea6617b621058cd0503805ba68bd6d21bab16 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Nadia Chambers <nadia.yvette.chambers@ik.me>
Date: Fri, 22 May 2026 12:31:42 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 122/174] fs/exec: align stack_top to MMUPAGE granularity, not
 PAGE

setup_arg_pages() rounded the user-supplied stack_top up to PAGE_SIZE
with PAGE_ALIGN. Under page clustering PAGE_SIZE > MMUPAGE_SIZE, so an
input that is MMUPAGE-aligned but not PAGE-aligned (the common case for
STACK_TOP_MAX on archs whose vdso/stack-guard arithmetic uses
MMUPAGE-granular sizes -- s390x is the canonical example) overshoots to
the next PAGE boundary, which is above STACK_TOP_MAX itself.

When that happens stack_shift = vma->vm_end - stack_top underflows to a
huge unsigned value. relocate_vma_down() then computes new_start =
old_start - stack_shift, which wraps to an address just above old_start,
and vma_expand() trips VM_WARN_ON_VMG(target->vm_start < vmg->start)
because it sees the original stack VMA extending below the bogus new
start. The maple tree is left holding a stale partial entry that a
subsequent validate_mm() catches as a BUG_ON.

Stack VMAs are MMUPAGE-aligned (their vm_end equals STACK_TOP_MAX, which
is computed from vdso_size() in MMUPAGE units). Aligning stack_top to
the same granularity matches the VMA layout and avoids the underflow.

Fixes intermittent maple_tree validate_mm BUG_ON during execve under
PGCL=4 on s390x; reproduced as 1/96 runs in a parallel matrix loop with
mm/vma.c instrumentation, and dropped to 0/36 (then 0/N in extended
verify) after this change.

Signed-off-by: Nadia Yvette Chambers <nadia.yvette.chambers@gmail.com>
---
 fs/exec.c | 4 ++--
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/fs/exec.c b/fs/exec.c
index ba12b4c466f6..6017b09603dd 100644
--- a/fs/exec.c
+++ b/fs/exec.c
@@ -626,14 +626,14 @@ int setup_arg_pages(struct linux_binprm *bprm,
 	if (vma->vm_end - vma->vm_start > stack_base)
 		return -ENOMEM;
 
-	stack_base = PAGE_ALIGN(stack_top - stack_base);
+	stack_base = MMUPAGE_ALIGN(stack_top - stack_base);
 
 	stack_shift = vma->vm_start - stack_base;
 	mm->arg_start = bprm->p - stack_shift;
 	bprm->p = vma->vm_end - stack_shift;
 #else
 	stack_top = arch_align_stack(stack_top);
-	stack_top = PAGE_ALIGN(stack_top);
+	stack_top = MMUPAGE_ALIGN(stack_top);
 
 	if (unlikely(stack_top < mmap_min_addr) ||
 	    unlikely(vma->vm_end - vma->vm_start >= stack_top - mmap_min_addr))
-- 
